    "name": "Nick Luscombe",
    "profile": "British DJ and compilation producer. \r\n\r\nLuscombe made his break through as the man behind XFM's influential \"Flo-Motion\" radio show which started in 2000. The show was a specialist show providing a blend of deep club music including broken beat, electronica, techno, house, and jazz. \r\n\r\nHe has compiled two Flo-Motion albums and has DJs in the UK, Europe, and Japan, including the Big Chill and V Music festivals. \r\n\r\nFrom January 2007 he moved to a Saturday night slot on Resonance FM. \r\n",
